<title>HUNGARY: Scala ECE says '96 revenues up 78 pct.</title>
<headline>Scala ECE says '96 revenues up 78 pct.</headline>
<dateline>BUDAPEST 1997-03-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hungary-based business software company Scala ECE said that net revenues for fiscal 1996 grew 78 percent from 1995 to $16.3 million.</p>
<p>Scala, which is listed on the Vienna stock exchange, said in a statement that fourth quarter sales were up 68 percent from the previous year, to $6.4 million.</p>
<p>Earnings per share grew 36 percent to $4.28 on the basis of 525,411 weighted average shares in issue in 1996. Software sales grew by 41 percent to $7.9 million while revenues from consulting rose 168 percent from 1995 to $5.9 million.</p>
